Battery degradation can be divided into shelf degradation (calendar fade) and cycle degradation [31]. Shelf degradation corresponds to the normal corrosion process, which is independent of its cycling behavior, and thus regarded as a constant [8]. Cycle degradation corresponds to the cycle regime, as discussed in Section 3.1. For a given time period, assumed to be a day, the battery degradation is set as the larger one between the shelf degradation and cycle degradation, as shown in (1). All the degradation is measured by a percentage reduction in the battery cycle life.1DP=maxDPcy,DPshelf\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
